<font face=Arial,Helvetica>
<b>Making money in a copyright-free world</b><br><font face=Arial,Helvetica size=1>Posted on  Sunday, August 06 @ 21:34:24 EDT

</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td bgcolor=ffffff>
<font face=Arial,Helvetica>
<a href=search.php3?query=&topic=20&author=><img src=images/topics/news.gif border=0 Alt="General News" align=right hspace=10 vspace=10></a>
<P>In today's column, <A href=http://www.liberzine.com/>Liberzine</A> editor Jerry Brito discusses <A href=http://www.liberzine.com/jerrybrito/000804bizmodels.htm>business models for artists and content creators</A> in a world without legal protection of intellectual property, including models similar to the <A href=http://www.firstmonday.dk/issues/issue4_6/kelsey/index.html>Street Performer's Protocol</A>, in which artists hold a piece of work until they have received a set number of pre-orders and then release the work into the public domain.</P>

<P>Are these business models the wave of the future?  What do you think of copyright and IP laws?</P> 
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</td>
</tr>
</table><br>

